WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

02:11.642 --> 02:13.443
Tell me!

02:14.929 --> 02:17.348
If you know what the ending
should be, then just tell me.

02:17.448 --> 02:20.817
- It just has to be surprising...
- Don't say surprising and inevitable.

02:24.921 --> 02:27.993
- But in this story, what does that mean?
- You've got her at the top of a building.

02:28.093 --> 02:31.729
She takes a step off.
You set up her belief in God.

02:31.829 --> 02:36.001
Some belief in some God she thinks will
catch her, and we hope it will catch her.

02:36.101 --> 02:38.803
So should she not jump,
or should she jump and be saved,

02:38.903 --> 02:40.138
caught by something
or someone or should...

02:40.238 --> 02:43.839
- Just has to be surprising and inevitable.
- Surprising and inevitable.

02:44.408 --> 02:47.512
- I'm sending it to you.
- Don't send it to me. Un-send it!

02:47.612 --> 02:49.528
You're trying to get me
to give you an ending.

02:49.628 --> 02:51.621
- I'm onto something.
- You're absolutely onto something.

02:51.721 --> 02:53.032
But you want some archetypal ending.

02:53.132 --> 02:55.411
If you're doing some "let him
figure it out" thing, spare me.

02:55.511 --> 02:58.789
I've been walking the earth for half
as long as you and I need some help.

02:58.889 --> 03:01.092
...the "archetypes"
and line them up and shoot them.

03:01.192 --> 03:04.929
- Don't rag on archetype construction.
- You can't tell a real story with any detail

03:05.029 --> 03:09.133
if you're a slave to some Joseph Campbell
one-size-fits-all mad lib

03:09.233 --> 03:12.868
that applies to everybody
on the face of the Earth.

03:12.969 --> 03:16.444
Are you feeling you're close and you're
wanting me to validate the work you've done,

03:16.544 --> 03:19.743
- or are you feeling that...
- I'm feeling that I'm shit.

03:19.843 --> 03:24.690
And I'm feeling you have the power to
make me slightly less shitty, and you won't.

03:28.118 --> 03:30.571
You are the least...

03:30.671 --> 03:33.747
shitty person...

03:34.647 --> 03:36.196
I know.

03:37.327 --> 03:39.827
- So why do I feel like...
- Because congratulations.

03:39.927 --> 03:42.631
- For what?
- You're a writer.

05:38.215 --> 05:41.452
- Thanks for giving us an early look.
- The kids just moved out.

05:41.552 --> 05:45.721
Don't worry, it's only June.
It'll air out over the summer.

05:49.293 --> 05:50.812
- What?
- What?

05:50.912 --> 05:52.780
- What?
- What, what?

05:52.930 --> 05:56.968
You know, I just gave this tour to the kid
who's going to be your roommate in the fall.

05:57.068 --> 05:59.770
You guys are so different.
What are you majoring in?

05:59.870 --> 06:02.572
- Writing.
- He's working on writing.

06:02.672 --> 06:07.197
- What's he studying? The roommate.
- Science, I think.

06:07.378 --> 06:09.045
Zero sense of humor.

06:11.264 --> 06:13.318
You'll have all summer
to get used to the idea.

06:13.418 --> 06:16.220
- I'm working on writing?
- Yes, you're learning to write.

06:16.320 --> 06:19.472
You're a writer who's writing
while he's learning to write.

06:20.157 --> 06:21.159
- Two, please.
- Three.

06:21.259 --> 06:22.710
- Sorry, three.
- Right this way.

06:22.810 --> 06:24.886
Thank you.

06:26.863 --> 06:28.900
- Jesus!
- You asked me to come to dinner.

06:29.000 --> 06:31.336
- You asked me to read it.
- It's like a bloodbath.

06:31.436 --> 06:34.038
- A lot of it's punctuation. You got a letter.
- It's a style.

06:34.138 --> 06:35.673
- Don't say Cormac McCarthy.
- Cormac McCarthy.

06:35.773 --> 06:39.644
He made a huge impact, but he wasn't
sending out work at your age.

06:39.744 --> 06:43.247
Unless you have a real idea about the ending,
it's time for me to start sending it out.

06:43.347 --> 06:46.150
You just said you need an idea.
You just said it's not ready.

06:46.250 --> 06:48.035
- I do need an idea.
- So?

06:48.135 --> 06:49.971
- So give me one.
- I don't have one.

06:50.071 --> 06:52.223
If you do, you owe it to me,
because I don't think you have any ideas

06:52.323 --> 06:54.792
with your critical voice
constantly inside my head.

06:54.892 --> 06:57.127
You guys fight like my parents.

06:57.227 --> 07:00.898
But they say that's what keeps them hot
for each other, so I guess it's okay.

07:00.998 --> 07:04.151
You've got six, at least four years
of school ahead of you.

07:04.251 --> 07:06.737
- You're not supposed to know how to...
- I sent it out.

07:06.837 --> 07:08.039
- No, you didn't.
- You sent what out?

07:08.139 --> 07:11.209
- Jump. My story, I sent it out.
- Where, to be rewritten?

07:11.309 --> 07:12.610
- Mean.
- Sorry.

07:12.710 --> 07:15.914
This could be a good story. Way down
the line it could, but it needs...

07:16.014 --> 07:17.899
- What, you?
- Mean.

07:17.999 --> 07:19.100
- Sorry.
- Your dad's cute.

07:19.250 --> 07:21.586
You know, I know I can't...
Mean, mean, mean.

07:21.686 --> 07:23.271
- Sorry, sorry, sorry.
- What's it about?

07:23.371 --> 07:25.156
You only get one shot with these places.

07:25.256 --> 07:27.992
It's about what goes through a woman's mind
from the time she jumps off a building

07:28.092 --> 07:29.894
until she lands and dies.

07:29.994 --> 07:31.829
- You opened my mail?
- She did.

07:31.929 --> 07:33.694
- You opened my mail?
- Where did you send it?

07:33.794 --> 07:36.498
- Why did you open...
- I thought you didn't have any siblings.

07:37.834 --> 07:40.088
Half-sibling. She's my half-sibling.

07:40.188 --> 07:42.540
- Where did you send it?
- You haven't heard of it.

07:42.640 --> 07:44.208
- Oh, God.
- It's an online literary.

07:44.308 --> 07:46.744
- What's the name of it? The web thing?
- You haven't... You haven't heard of it.

07:46.844 --> 07:50.415
Try me. Fertile... something?
Bitter, whatever it is?

07:50.515 --> 07:53.818
- Subtly very mean.
- I'm sorry, tell me. I'll be good.

07:53.918 --> 07:55.286
- Blow Back.
- Gesundheit.

07:55.386 --> 07:56.837
- So?
- I'll have a chardonnay.

07:56.937 --> 07:58.823
- Me too.
- And a glass of red wine.

07:58.923 --> 08:00.525
- May I see some identif...
- They're for me.

08:00.625 --> 08:03.058
- All of them?
- It's a stressful time.

08:03.560 --> 08:05.597
You're leaving home. I'm shaken up too.

08:05.697 --> 08:08.600
- I'm not leaving home.
- You're going away to college.

08:08.700 --> 08:09.901
I'm not going away.

08:10.001 --> 08:13.135
Don't be ridiculous.
After the summer, you're g...

08:14.187 --> 08:18.035
One, two, three, four... 43, 44, 45...

08:18.135 --> 08:20.077
- 67, 68, 69.
- Okay.

08:20.177 --> 08:21.312
- 70, 71...
- Okay.

08:21.412 --> 08:23.468
76, 77...

08:23.568 --> 08:25.636
82, 83, 84, 85.

08:25.736 --> 08:27.471
- Mr. and Mrs. Durning?
- What's your point?

08:27.571 --> 08:31.142
I'm moving 85 steps away from you.
That doesn't rate as going away to college.

08:31.242 --> 08:33.057
- Do you want me to move across the park?
- Stop it!

08:33.157 --> 08:36.681
What am I doing?
You asked me to read it, I read it.

08:36.780 --> 08:39.350
I'm giving you my advice
as one adult to another.

08:39.450 --> 08:41.818
Why are you getting so upset?
I thought we were both adults.

08:41.919 --> 08:43.320
- We are, but it's different.
- Why?

08:43.419 --> 08:47.577
Because one adult came out
of the other adult's vagina!

08:48.525 --> 08:50.259
What?

08:57.800 --> 09:01.499
- Maybe I'll see you.
- Yeah, okay, bye.

09:09.580 --> 09:12.648
- She seems nice.
- She's awful.

09:16.453 --> 09:20.758
- There's something wrong with us.
- It's not just us. Nobody sleeps anymore.

09:20.858 --> 09:23.476
Besides, I'm not going to watch it
without you, so if you don't either,

09:23.576 --> 09:25.596
we'll have a six-week break
while you're in California.

09:25.696 --> 09:28.530
<i>If I can just spot
the triggering mechanism...</i>

09:28.932 --> 09:30.656
<i>Hello.</i>

09:35.905 --> 09:37.968
<i>It seems louder over here.</i>

09:38.068 --> 09:40.375
<i>Hand me that candle, will you?</i>

09:43.613 --> 09:48.016
Put ze candle back.

10:03.067 --> 10:04.724
<i>Wait.</i>

10:07.070 --> 10:10.639
<i>Wait. Where are you going?</i>

10:11.241 --> 10:13.844
<i>I was gonna make a pretzel.</i>

10:14.544 --> 10:17.415
Your dad's picking you up
at the airport. It'll be fun.

10:17.515 --> 10:20.450
Step-family. It'll be step-fun.

10:20.550 --> 10:21.919
- Oh, crap, crap, crap!
- What?

10:22.019 --> 10:23.550
- I forgot my...
- What did you need? No, I can get it.

10:23.650 --> 10:25.854
Just don't, don't, don't!

10:28.458 --> 10:30.814
Jesus, Jackie.

10:32.596 --> 10:33.698
Why won't it be fun?

10:33.798 --> 10:35.166
- Taxi?
- Yes, please.

10:35.266 --> 10:38.001
Your father looks happy. He looks sweet.

10:38.101 --> 10:41.371
- What does that mean?
- Where's your suitcase.

10:41.471 --> 10:44.542
For the summer? Is there anything
other than shorts in there? Pants?

10:44.642 --> 10:47.279
Do they even wear pants in California
when they're not...

10:47.379 --> 10:49.913
- Yes?
- Whatever. Shoes?

10:50.013 --> 10:54.785
Flip flops? Can you walk in those things?
What am I saying, nobody walks out there.

10:54.885 --> 10:56.788
- Can you drive in them?
- Not that you would know.

10:56.888 --> 11:00.091
- Many people don't drive.
- I don't drive.

11:00.191 --> 11:02.856
What about books? What will you read
during the day or at night?

11:02.956 --> 11:06.230
- What will you read at night?
- Maybe I won't read. Maybe I'll watch TV.

11:06.330 --> 11:10.686
Maybe I won't do anything at all except
stare into space, relax and breathe.

11:11.785 --> 11:13.589
Jesus.

11:14.485 --> 11:16.977
- What line'd you call?
- <i>I sent you On The Town.</i>

11:17.077 --> 11:19.526
- I just got it.
- <i>What'd you think of it?</i>

11:19.626 --> 11:22.046
- I just got it.
- <i>What'd you think?</i>

11:22.146 --> 11:25.483
I think it's long and full of adverbs.
Should I come in?

11:25.583 --> 11:27.685
<i>No, no. Read it. I'll hang up.</i>

11:27.785 --> 11:30.788
- I'll call you as soon as I'm done.
- <i>No, I need to know I can reach you.</i>

11:30.888 --> 11:33.128
- I'm here. You can reach me here.
- <i>No, I...</i>

11:33.228 --> 11:37.094
I'm going to give you your own special
ringtone so I always know it's you.

11:37.194 --> 11:40.298
<i>Yeah, but later, what hap...
Like, what, what if...</i>

11:40.398 --> 11:44.266
On and in my hand. Reachable.

11:44.718 --> 11:45.776
Always.

11:45.903 --> 11:47.719
Excuse me.

11:52.208 --> 11:55.410
<i>What did you mean about Dad being sweet?</i>

11:55.579 --> 11:58.632
- <i>Just what I said.</i>
- <i>You just meant that he's sweet?</i>

11:58.732 --> 12:01.585
- <i>Unless something goes wrong.</i>
- <i>Then what is he?</i>

12:01.685 --> 12:03.588
How do I know that
I can reach you at any time?

12:03.688 --> 12:05.722
<i>Not around.</i>

12:05.822 --> 12:07.992
I need to know that you are reachable.

12:08.292 --> 12:11.377
Hey, I'm heading out. Thank you.

12:11.827 --> 12:14.560
- Have fun. Where are you going?
- Aruba.

12:14.660 --> 12:17.067
- Nice.
- My wife's mother's coming with us.

12:17.167 --> 12:18.908
Mothers are awful.

12:19.268 --> 12:22.273
<i>I have plans later, so if I don't answer,
we'll talk when we talk.</i>

12:22.373 --> 12:23.608
<i>Talk when we talk?</i>

12:23.908 --> 12:27.789
- <i>Who is this? Plans?</i>
- <i>No, not those kinds of...</i>

12:27.889 --> 12:31.317
<i>I don't know and I don't want to know
how many years it's been,</i>

12:31.417 --> 12:35.419
<i>but at some point, I think it's actually
bad for you not to have...</i>

12:35.519 --> 12:39.156
<i>plans. For your health, I mean.
Powering down.</i>

12:39.256 --> 12:43.325
What is the matter with you?
I need to have a definite answer.

12:48.225 --> 12:52.086
- On and in my hand. Reachable always.
- Everyone needs a little peace...

12:52.186 --> 12:53.922
<i>I don't really have plans.
Call me when you land.</i>

12:54.098 --> 12:55.913
Everybody... <i>You there?</i>

12:56.013 --> 12:58.406
- What?
- Peace.

13:56.165 --> 13:59.768
No, no, no, no, no, no! I was waiting!

13:59.904 --> 14:02.425
You're a horrible man!

14:52.957 --> 14:55.925
- Hello?
- Oh, hello?

14:56.025 --> 14:58.061
- How...
- Peter, how are you?

14:58.161 --> 15:02.032
I'm doing great. No complaints.
I'm doing great.

15:02.132 --> 15:04.501
Well, good. I'm so glad.

15:04.601 --> 15:05.861
- What?
- What?

15:05.961 --> 15:09.206
- Did you say "well?"
- You're doing well. Not "great."

15:09.306 --> 15:11.931
- "Well." Anyway, I'm so glad.
- Who are you talking to?

15:12.031 --> 15:14.211
- Talking to Angelo's mama.
- May I talk to her?

15:14.311 --> 15:16.146
- <i>That's okay, she doesn't have t...</i>
- Hi.

15:16.246 --> 15:18.614
- Hello, how are you?
- Good.

15:20.583 --> 15:23.153
- So what have you been up to?
- Playing.

15:23.253 --> 15:25.171
- <i>How's that going?</i>
- Good.

15:25.271 --> 15:26.740
- Well.
- What?

15:26.840 --> 15:29.359
- Nothing.
- What are you doing?

15:29.459 --> 15:33.764
Working. Editing. I have deadlines.

15:33.864 --> 15:38.299
- I'm in fiction, but still they want...
- My mommy has a baby in her tummy.

15:41.838 --> 15:43.972
Hi, hello.

15:44.440 --> 15:47.544
You haven't answered your phone.
It's been five days.

15:47.644 --> 15:50.238
- Why haven't you answered y...
- What's up?

15:50.847 --> 15:53.287
What's up?

15:53.387 --> 15:55.517
Yeah, you doing okay?

15:56.152 --> 15:57.565
Yeah.

15:58.054 --> 16:00.914
<i>I'm doing... great.</i>

16:16.138 --> 16:18.742
I promise you this is the last time
I'll bother you till the fall.

16:18.842 --> 16:22.346
I'll lay it on the floor, pick it up
and go. I just want to see if it fits.

16:22.446 --> 16:24.347
He's going to kill me
for starting to decorate,

16:24.447 --> 16:26.484
but I also know if the room
looks nice, he's more likely to...

16:26.584 --> 16:28.293
He dropped out.

16:40.762 --> 16:43.267
<i>I hope you take a moment
before you react to this.</i>

16:43.667 --> 16:46.003
<i>This is not something I'm doing lightly.</i>

16:46.403 --> 16:49.138
<i>School and frankly New York City...</i>

16:49.238 --> 16:50.706
<i>Are you sitting down?</i>

16:51.441 --> 16:53.275
<i>They're not for me.</i>

16:55.134 --> 16:56.945
Thank you.

17:14.463 --> 17:17.065
- Miss Durning.
- I'll follow you.

17:26.075 --> 17:29.580
Do you have a power port?
I need to charge my laptop and my phone.

17:29.680 --> 17:31.048
I do have one, yes, ma'am.

17:31.148 --> 17:34.749
I'll need you for a few hours.
More than a few. Are you free?

17:35.918 --> 17:38.592
- I told them it was "as directed."
- No problem.

17:41.391 --> 17:45.380
It's still in there, and the issue
goes to print in three hours.

17:45.629 --> 17:46.964
Regular.

17:47.064 --> 17:50.463
I don't want to live in a world where a cup
of coffee has to be described as regular

17:50.563 --> 17:53.370
unless it's 1940 and the guy
means cream and sugar.

17:53.470 --> 17:55.806
- <i>Where are you?</i>
- On my way to a meeting.

17:55.906 --> 17:57.240
- <i>Where?</i>
- West Side.

17:57.340 --> 18:00.243
- <i>I want you to look at it.</i>
- Send it to me, I'll get it on my phone.

18:01.656 --> 18:03.333
Got it.

18:15.091 --> 18:17.709
3550, there it is.

18:19.896 --> 18:21.949
That's a nice house.

18:22.432 --> 18:24.434
Yes, ma'am, it is.

18:25.296 --> 18:27.605
No, no, no, get in, get in, get...
get back in, get back in the car.

18:27.705 --> 18:30.288
- Ma'am?
- Get in.

18:38.514 --> 18:42.351
Ma'am, any idea how long we'll be here?

18:42.451 --> 18:46.414
I just have to see about something.
Shouldn't take long.

19:09.479 --> 19:11.214
Jesus!

19:11.314 --> 19:14.516
Yeah, they come out of the hills
'cause they're thirsty.

19:17.720 --> 19:19.995
This place is terrifying.

19:25.761 --> 19:28.196
Is that who you're waiting for?

19:33.937 --> 19:35.605
Follow him.

19:35.705 --> 19:37.459
- Ma'am?
- Follow him, follow him, follow him.

19:49.051 --> 19:51.085
Go slower.

19:52.438 --> 19:54.639
Go slower, slow down.

19:55.225 --> 19:57.034
And pull over.

20:06.602 --> 20:07.971
- Wetsuits?
- Ma'am?

20:08.071 --> 20:12.109
Californians have such thin skin. I'd like
to see one of them try to swim back east.

20:12.209 --> 20:13.871
- The water can get kind of...
- What is your name?

20:13.971 --> 20:17.478
- Ramon.
- Ramon, where is the ladies' room?

20:18.047 --> 20:22.852
Well, they're there, but I think
they're closed or broken or something.

20:22.952 --> 20:25.823
- Somewhere, there must be some place...
- Just those, I think.

20:25.923 --> 20:28.308
That's ridiculous.
Where do these people pee?

20:28.408 --> 20:33.206
I don't know for positive, but can't they
just go in their suits? Warms them up.

20:52.242 --> 20:54.731
<i>No, yo sé, si.
No, yo trabajé toda la noche.</i>

21:02.592 --> 21:03.770
<i>Sí, yo te llamo después.</i>

21:52.508 --> 21:54.277
Oh, shit!

21:54.377 --> 21:56.479
Shit, shit, shit!

21:56.579 --> 21:58.490
Shit!

22:12.428 --> 22:15.965
- What's he doing?
- Looking for a job?

22:16.065 --> 22:17.832
Thanks.

22:31.814 --> 22:34.315
Follow him, follow him, follow him.

22:36.652 --> 22:38.788
<i>Leave a message at the tone.</i>

22:38.888 --> 22:41.758
Oh, come on.
You haven't called me all day.

22:41.858 --> 22:44.511
Where are you?
I know you read what I sent.

22:44.611 --> 22:46.029
Get closer.

22:46.129 --> 22:49.896
- I like to keep one car length...
- Closer, closer, closer, closer, closer.

22:51.567 --> 22:52.769
I want to start a new life here,

22:52.869 --> 22:56.871
but that doesn't mean there has to be
this kind of distance between us.

23:00.276 --> 23:01.725
<i>Call me.</i>

23:06.349 --> 23:08.151
- Get closer.
- <i>We both need to make an effort here.</i>

23:08.251 --> 23:10.685
To be honest, ma'am,
I really think I'm close enough.

23:12.521 --> 23:16.824
God damn it! I just got rear ended
by some asshole tailgater!

23:24.200 --> 23:26.228
Jesus!

23:29.905 --> 23:30.874
I'm very sorry, sir.

23:30.974 --> 23:34.177
- It's okay. Will you step out of the car...
- You two have to pull over!

23:34.277 --> 23:36.343
Is anyone else in the car?

23:48.657 --> 23:50.827
- What happened?
- Are you kidding me?

23:50.927 --> 23:53.429
Jesus, it's so bright!

23:53.529 --> 23:56.364
You need to get these cars
off the street!

23:56.899 --> 24:00.537
Don't act like I'm the only crazy one.
What are you doing here?

24:00.637 --> 24:02.172
I'm living my life.

24:02.272 --> 24:05.608
- Here, I will live and work and...
- What, ride around on that thing?

24:05.708 --> 24:07.711
Many great writers
didn't believe in academia.

24:07.811 --> 24:09.967
- Name three.
- Hemingway, Gore Vidal...

24:10.067 --> 24:12.916
- That's two.
- I am choking. Do you understand?

24:13.016 --> 24:15.452
- In that city, in that apartment!
- Don't be dramatic.

24:15.552 --> 24:19.256
I'm choking on the women there.
These soulless free-floating heads.

24:19.356 --> 24:22.282
And every encounter I have with one
makes me want to be celibate

24:22.382 --> 24:25.428
- for the rest of my life.
- And the problem with that would be...

24:25.528 --> 24:27.331
- This is unhealthy.
- It was a joke.

24:27.431 --> 24:30.634
Jesus, I was joking!
That's the problem with Los Angeles.

24:30.734 --> 24:34.737
When they don't educate you,
and they don't educate you,

24:34.837 --> 24:39.009
you fail to develop the brain receptors
needed to have a fucking sense of humor!

24:39.109 --> 24:40.777
You have one. I've seen it.

24:40.877 --> 24:44.081
But you get out here
and on that thing and you lose it.

24:44.181 --> 24:46.416
You lose the power of reason.

24:46.516 --> 24:49.386
- Your father's just fine with this?
- You don't want to know.

24:49.486 --> 24:52.221
- What did he say?
- Just be happy.

24:52.321 --> 24:55.555
That's the stupidest thing I've ever heard.
What's wrong with our apartment?

24:55.655 --> 24:58.215
Cleaned out the closet lately?

24:58.815 --> 25:01.718
You want me back there so you can
watch me miserably struggle over something

25:01.818 --> 25:04.935
- that I'll never do just right.
- Nobody does it "just right."

25:05.035 --> 25:06.921
And you shit on me
for getting on a surfboard,

25:07.021 --> 25:09.806
something you could never do
because you might get your hair wet!

25:09.906 --> 25:13.009
- And by the way, I sleep out here.
- Of course you do, it's Los Angeles.

25:13.109 --> 25:16.280
- There's no reason to get out of bed!
- Oh, my God!

25:16.380 --> 25:17.714
Go back to New York.

25:17.814 --> 25:20.417
Swim laps in a chlorinated pool
50 stories up in the air.

25:20.517 --> 25:23.186
Do whatever you want. I don't care!
You know why?

25:23.286 --> 25:25.722
Because you're not interesting
to me anymore.

25:25.822 --> 25:27.958
This is interesting to me.

25:28.058 --> 25:32.293
And this is interesting to me,
and you could never do it.

25:42.905 --> 25:45.792
Don't doubt yourself. We told the guy
to write what he knows and he did.

25:45.892 --> 25:48.324
I would tell your young copy editor
that the only other choice

25:48.424 --> 25:50.366
at this late date is a very thin story

25:50.466 --> 25:52.127
- about a heartbroken pigeon.
- <i>Send it by me.</i>

25:52.227 --> 25:56.686
I'll send you the draft now and I'll
call you with the final in three... six.

25:56.786 --> 25:58.321
- <i>Where are you now?</i>
- I'm at lunch.

25:58.421 --> 26:00.957
- <i>Where?</i>
- Midtown. I'm reachable.

26:01.057 --> 26:05.027
- You've never done this before?
- No, but I'm in very good physical condition.

26:05.127 --> 26:06.596
You must have a lot of money.

26:06.696 --> 26:10.900
You're staying in a nice hotel,
you've hired me for a second day in a row.

26:11.000 --> 26:14.771
- I think you should get an instructor.
- I don't need some illiterate teenager

26:14.871 --> 26:18.274
telling me how to lie on my belly
and splash my arms in the water.

26:18.374 --> 26:20.339
I live in the most
challenging city in the country.

26:20.439 --> 26:23.013
I can navigate a few small waves
in sunny Santa Monica.

26:23.113 --> 26:25.346
That goes on your leg.

26:27.583 --> 26:32.622
I swim 400 meters three times a week.
I've swum in Long Island Sound.

26:32.722 --> 26:35.525
I've leaned half my body over a yacht
to pull my wallet out of the Hudson.

26:35.625 --> 26:37.892
You don't have to worry about me.

26:42.932 --> 26:45.091
Freezing in here!

27:14.163 --> 27:15.432
Couldn't you please get a teacher?

27:15.532 --> 27:18.435
Do I think I'm going to be great
the first few times I do it? No.

27:18.535 --> 27:20.180
- We could ask one of those guys.
- I know plenty of people

27:20.280 --> 27:23.738
who have taught themselves various sports
and they've done just fine.

27:30.279 --> 27:32.409
Could we have a signal?

27:32.509 --> 27:34.008
What are you talking about?

27:34.108 --> 27:36.653
I'm responsible for your safety
while you have me on the clock.

27:36.753 --> 27:38.321
- No you're not.
- Well, irregardless...

27:38.421 --> 27:39.823
- Oh, my God.
- What?

27:39.923 --> 27:41.468
- There's no such word.
- What?

27:41.568 --> 27:45.480
- Go on.
- Could we agree on an arm signal?

27:45.580 --> 27:48.896
So if you're in trouble out there,
I can do something.

27:50.833 --> 27:52.669
It's not your job, but yes.

27:52.769 --> 27:56.604
If you see me give the international
S.O.S. sign,

27:56.705 --> 27:59.707
it'd be very kind of you to call 9-1...

28:02.312 --> 28:04.847
- What is happening?
- I think you need a lesson.

28:04.947 --> 28:09.818
What I need is for someone to get
this thing out past these first few waves.

28:21.364 --> 28:23.032
You want to try it?

28:23.132 --> 28:25.902
Hello, my name is Jackie Durning.

28:26.002 --> 28:30.340
Would you do me the tremendous favor
of allowing me to pay you money

28:30.740 --> 28:33.183
to take my surfboard and...

28:33.283 --> 28:36.880
pull it or push it out there
just past those first few waves?

28:36.980 --> 28:40.183
Once you're out there, I'll swim to you.
I'm an excellent swimmer.

28:40.283 --> 28:44.254
I'll take the board from you
and you can come in and resume...

28:44.354 --> 28:47.290
- What? Doing nothing?
- Pretty much.

28:47.390 --> 28:50.130
- Will you do it?
- Okay.

28:54.163 --> 28:55.590
- Right, here I go.
- Remember.

28:55.690 --> 28:59.769
Yes, yes. I remember. I know it sounds
like hubris, but once I get out there,

28:59.869 --> 29:03.538
I really think I'm going to be better
than average at intuiting how to do this.

29:19.731 --> 29:21.756
Thank you very much.

29:28.665 --> 29:31.034
Darn it. Sorry.

29:31.134 --> 29:33.301
Poor planning on my part.

29:33.401 --> 29:36.491
I'm going to have my driver give you money.
Would $30 be all right?

29:36.591 --> 29:38.255
Yeah.

29:49.585 --> 29:51.119
What?

30:00.362 --> 30:04.100
Help! I'm coming! Lifeguard, lifeguard!

30:04.200 --> 30:05.901
Help!

30:06.001 --> 30:08.705
No! No!

30:08.805 --> 30:11.690
Lifeguard, help!

30:12.107 --> 30:14.444
- No, you idiot, I'm fine!
- Help!

30:14.544 --> 30:16.387
That wasn't it!

30:24.820 --> 30:27.114
I'm fine!

30:32.261 --> 30:35.665
- Let's get you back to shore.
- I just got out here.

30:36.065 --> 30:39.503
Well, just to be safe, show me you can put
your leash on and get back on your board.

30:39.603 --> 30:42.870
- I can.
- Great. Show me.

30:53.950 --> 30:55.817
It's possible I can't.

31:08.797 --> 31:11.601
- I didn't need any help. I was fine.
- You're welcome.

31:11.701 --> 31:14.536
- Maybe this man could give you a lesson.
- I don't need a lesson.

31:30.947 --> 31:34.580
<i>Gore Vidal was an Olympic athlete,
slept with men and fought in a world war.</i>

31:34.680 --> 31:37.259
<i>Talk to me when you've done
even one of those...</i>

32:07.856 --> 32:10.390
I want to surf like that.

32:39.221 --> 32:42.091
You just bailed?
Our parents would freak.

32:42.191 --> 32:44.094
Your parents were fine
with you leaving school?

32:44.694 --> 32:46.821
- My dad was.
- Not your mom?

32:48.793 --> 32:53.543
<i>Hemingway was in the army, lived
all over the world and shot himself!</i>

32:53.643 --> 32:56.904
She's had a slightly harder time
adjusting to the idea.

33:24.833 --> 33:27.370
The weather in this God-forsaken place!

33:27.470 --> 33:29.505
Most people put their wetsuits on
at the beach.

33:29.605 --> 33:33.373
Good for them. It took me 20 minutes and
someone from housekeeping to get into it.

33:33.473 --> 33:35.178
- Yes, I'm here.
- <i>What's wrong with it?</i>

33:35.278 --> 33:37.613
Page 17 of the proofs.

33:37.713 --> 33:41.951
"Gender". Feels like he wanted to write
"sex", but was too spineless to do it.

33:42.051 --> 33:43.878
- I can hear you fine.
- <i>Where are you?</i>

33:43.978 --> 33:47.490
In a taxi, downtown. Way down.

33:47.590 --> 33:50.409
In fact, I'm heading into a tunnel,
so it's possible we'll...

33:50.509 --> 33:53.343
Fill this out and sign, please.

34:01.720 --> 34:03.606
- Your age?
- I'm sorry.

34:03.706 --> 34:05.742
- What's your age?
- What's your age?

34:05.842 --> 34:08.812
- Thirty seven.
- Yeah, good. Me too.

34:08.911 --> 34:11.505
- Good morning.
- Hey.

34:15.117 --> 34:18.721
Just so you know, another driver will be
arriving during your lesson to pick you up.

34:18.821 --> 34:21.123
- Why?
- I'm not available after 1:30, ma'am.

34:21.224 --> 34:24.056
- Why?
- Professional reasons.

34:25.994 --> 34:28.965
I have to get my kids from school.
All of them.

34:29.065 --> 34:31.668
- 'Cause I missed two days.
- Pick them up and come back.

34:31.768 --> 34:34.437
I won't have to meet someone new
and you can stay on the clock.

34:34.536 --> 34:36.734
The limo company won't lose anything.
They never have to know.

34:36.833 --> 34:38.875
You don't want my kids in the back
yelling and throwing stuff.

34:38.975 --> 34:40.310
I'll see you when I'm done.

34:41.010 --> 34:44.945
Okay, Jackie. Lie down
on your surfboard for me.

34:55.524 --> 34:58.492
Good. Paddle your arms.

35:00.795 --> 35:02.553
- Is there a problem?
- I understand, I'll paddle.

35:02.653 --> 35:05.966
I don't have to do it now.
I'm lying in the dirt.

35:06.602 --> 35:08.371
Okay.

35:08.471 --> 35:13.109
Well, after you're done paddling, place
your hands on either side of your chest,

35:13.209 --> 35:14.810
push up arching your back.

35:14.910 --> 35:18.915
And a lot of beginners start
on one knee and then stand up.

35:19.015 --> 35:24.853
For later, what you're going
to do is jump or pop up.

35:24.953 --> 35:27.721
- Now?
- Why not now?

35:34.563 --> 35:36.797
Good, try it again.

35:39.667 --> 35:41.470
Okay, there's no need to rush to pop up.

35:41.570 --> 35:43.239
I'd rather just learn
the right way from the beginning.

35:43.339 --> 35:44.425
This isn't the wrong way...

35:44.525 --> 35:47.308
I'm sorry, it hasn't stopped.
I think I answered it.

35:47.676 --> 35:49.444
Yes, what?

35:49.544 --> 35:52.220
I do stand by it.
The Flowers That Flowered?

35:52.320 --> 35:55.161
Seriously? There's whimsy,
and then there's whatever that is.

35:55.261 --> 35:59.255
My phone is on. Turn off my phone.
What were you saying?

35:59.355 --> 36:00.489
Here's the deal, Jackie.

36:00.589 --> 36:04.327
We are going to put this inanimate object
into an ever-changing environment.

36:04.427 --> 36:06.961
- Hey, you.
- Hey, you.

36:07.061 --> 36:09.165
The surfboard does nothing on its own.

36:09.793 --> 36:12.811
It only moves if this ever-changing
environment moves it,

36:12.911 --> 36:16.606
or if you, who are also
ever changing, make it move.

36:16.706 --> 36:18.808
- Do you understand?
- Yes, obviously, I...

36:18.908 --> 36:22.044
The ocean moves over a sandy floor
that we cannot see.

36:22.144 --> 36:25.375
When the shape of that floor rises,
a wave is formed,

36:25.475 --> 36:28.201
and that wave moves towards
the shore, do you understand?

36:28.301 --> 36:30.019
I'm not stupid.
If you can understand it...

36:30.119 --> 36:33.756
That wave moving toward the shore
will also move anything in its path.

36:33.856 --> 36:37.286
If you or the object are in its way,
it will hit you.

36:37.386 --> 36:40.843
Therefore, the safest place
you can be in the water is where?

36:42.302 --> 36:45.868
The safest place to be given that you
and the object are ever-changing?

36:45.968 --> 36:48.335
At home watching 20/20?

36:49.404 --> 36:52.873
- Can I have some water?
- We're going to paddle out to there.

36:53.775 --> 36:57.113
When I tell you to, you're going to paddle
to where the wave is breaking.

36:57.213 --> 36:59.448
If you're lucky enough to catch a wave,

36:59.548 --> 37:03.886
you'll stand up, placing your feet evenly
over the center line of the surfboard

37:03.986 --> 37:05.821
and ride that wave toward shore.

37:05.921 --> 37:10.526
If you're that lucky, well, then lower
yourself back down onto the surfboard,

37:10.626 --> 37:13.362
turn around and paddle back to me.

37:13.562 --> 37:17.765
Whatever happens,
you do as I say, understand?

37:20.802 --> 37:23.637
We can skip it and go back
if you're too freaked out.

37:24.839 --> 37:26.707
Let's go.

37:30.111 --> 37:34.650
The most dangerous part of surfing
is entering and exiting the water.

37:34.750 --> 37:39.202
What happens if this object comes between
you and an oncoming wave?

37:39.302 --> 37:40.322
What?

37:40.422 --> 37:44.858
- What happens if this inanimate object...
- For God's sake...

37:46.428 --> 37:48.962
Get on your board.

37:56.738 --> 37:59.430
Oh, my God!

38:00.175 --> 38:01.644
Tiring, isn't it?

38:01.744 --> 38:04.680
- Can we take a break?
- We are inside.

38:04.780 --> 38:06.782
- You know what that means?
- No.

38:06.882 --> 38:09.435
- We are in the impact zone.
- Oh, please.

38:09.535 --> 38:11.020
- Pardon?
- Nothing. Go ahead.

38:11.120 --> 38:15.490
If we stay here, we'll be hit by every
single wave that comes in

38:15.590 --> 38:18.392
and get tumbled in the white water.

38:19.427 --> 38:24.300
So we're going to go outside,
or beyond the breaking wave.

38:24.400 --> 38:25.967
See that one?

38:26.367 --> 38:29.071
- We're going to paddle beyond that.
- I can't.

38:29.171 --> 38:31.973
- You have to.
- Says who?

38:32.073 --> 38:34.108
Nobody's ever asked me that before.

38:37.512 --> 38:39.579
What is that?

38:40.560 --> 38:41.770
- Freak set.
- What?

38:41.870 --> 38:44.253
Bigger set of waves
than we've seen before.

38:44.353 --> 38:47.554
- Well, what do I do?
- Do you have children?

38:47.989 --> 38:50.418
- What did you say?
- Do you have a child?

38:50.518 --> 38:51.601
Yes.

38:51.701 --> 38:55.392
Paddle as if your child's life
depends on it.

38:55.797 --> 38:59.059
Paddle, Jackie. Paddle down hard.

39:06.241 --> 39:08.232
Good job.

39:09.711 --> 39:13.210
Boy, from this angle it doesn't look
so bad. I thought it was bigger...

39:20.455 --> 39:22.945
Get back on your board.

39:24.759 --> 39:27.561
Get on top of your surfboard.

39:30.866 --> 39:32.668
Sit up.

39:34.836 --> 39:36.478
Do you own an egg beater?

39:37.572 --> 39:38.607
I'm begging you.

39:38.707 --> 39:41.205
Assuming you've at least seen
an egg beater,

39:41.305 --> 39:43.980
I want you to move your ass
to the back of the board,

39:44.080 --> 39:47.016
hold onto the rail,
egg beater your legs around.

39:47.116 --> 39:50.586
I can turn the surfboard around.
Is this really the best use of our time?

39:51.386 --> 39:54.187
Why don't you try to turn
the board around your way?

39:54.289 --> 39:56.557
For God's sake!

40:16.277 --> 40:18.912
Can you explain it one more time?

40:19.681 --> 40:21.570
Slide back.

40:21.923 --> 40:24.986
Hold on. Egg-beater your legs.

40:27.522 --> 40:29.990
Good, do it again.

40:30.925 --> 40:33.193
Good, other way.

40:35.029 --> 40:37.834
It'll be to your benefit
to be able to do that quickly.

40:38.234 --> 40:40.469
- In general?
- Nope, now.

40:40.869 --> 40:43.972
Slide back, egg-beater your legs,

40:44.072 --> 40:46.008
paddle towards shore.

40:46.108 --> 40:50.829
If you catch it, stand up, bend your knees
and ride the wave towards shore.

40:50.929 --> 40:53.402
If you fall off, cover your head
and fall flat.

40:53.502 --> 40:55.651
You don't know what's on the bottom.
You hear me?

40:55.751 --> 40:58.285
- Yes, yes, whatever!
- One, two, three!

42:03.017 --> 42:05.709
Good job. Call me
if you want another lesson.

42:33.362 --> 42:35.079
<i>Hijo!</i>

42:40.288 --> 42:41.690
<i>Dickens!</i>

42:41.790 --> 42:44.458
- <i>Look who's texting!</i>
- <i>Dickens!</i>

42:44.558 --> 42:48.053
<i>Dickens wrote soap operas and was maniac
depressive. You don't want to be him.</i>

42:48.153 --> 42:49.731
<i>Heard from "Blow Hard"?</i>

42:49.831 --> 42:52.332
<i>Mean. Sorry. Blow Back?</i>

42:53.034 --> 42:54.855
Thank you.

43:01.176 --> 43:03.111
- Did you go out?
- Yeah.

43:03.211 --> 43:06.980
- How was it?
- It was okay. Closed out.

43:07.315 --> 43:09.716
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

43:15.857 --> 43:17.893
Did you go out?

43:18.193 --> 43:20.060
I did.

43:20.662 --> 43:22.729
Closed out, right?

43:23.064 --> 43:24.267
Beautiful.

43:24.867 --> 43:28.135
Every day I'm out there
is absolutely beautiful.

43:34.208 --> 43:36.778
- Have you read this?
- I have.

43:36.878 --> 43:39.454
- It's supposed to be amazing.
- Is that for school?

43:39.554 --> 43:43.049
- No, for fun.
- Well, then you might actually enjoy it.

43:43.985 --> 43:46.071
What are you reading?

43:46.850 --> 43:50.590
A little bit of the world,
a little bit of pleasure.

43:51.325 --> 43:55.262
- Anything to avoid writing.
- You're a writer?

43:56.578 --> 44:01.803
Oh, my God, you are so lucky,
to write in a place like this.

44:01.903 --> 44:03.437
I am lucky.

44:06.724 --> 44:10.393
Can I ask you a question? Do you work?

44:11.145 --> 44:13.355
I'm sorry, I mean,
like, to survive, do you...

44:13.455 --> 44:16.916
I work, but I work to live,
not the other way around.

44:22.223 --> 44:25.025
I'm sort of stuck lately.

44:26.094 --> 44:29.298
How do you write here with the ocean
and the sunlight right outside?

44:29.398 --> 44:31.931
I have to agonize in a dark room.

44:32.600 --> 44:35.101
Yeah, I don't agonize.

44:38.122 --> 44:40.728
<i>I have an idea for your story.</i>

44:45.313 --> 44:47.199
This is an ever-changing environment,

44:47.299 --> 44:49.032
- so while we're out...
- Not again.

44:49.884 --> 44:51.918
You know a better way?

44:53.955 --> 44:57.624
Cover your head when you fall. Let's go.

45:37.131 --> 45:40.533
Hey! Who raised you, you ins...

46:13.734 --> 46:14.665
- Hello...
- What is it?

46:14.765 --> 46:17.105
- That's how you say hello?
- What's the idea?

46:18.247 --> 46:20.310
That's work calling.
Let's meet somewhere and...

46:20.410 --> 46:22.191
- You're still in LA?
- So?

46:22.291 --> 46:25.083
I've sent the story out.
Maybe you're right. Maybe no one will call.

46:25.183 --> 46:27.926
- I'm not going to agonize.
- You're going to agonize. You're a writer.

46:28.026 --> 46:30.168
It's agony.
I've never heard such a ridiculous...

46:30.268 --> 46:32.820
- I'll call you back.
- Don't call me back.

46:32.920 --> 46:37.393
- Dropout who reads Marquez. Cool.
- Yeah, they'll never get that.

46:37.493 --> 46:41.263
- They?
- My parents. Well, my mother.

46:41.363 --> 46:44.118
Once it's not being shoved down
your throat, you want to read it.

46:44.218 --> 46:48.203
Yeah, she's never going to get that.
I was lucky. Second kid.

46:48.303 --> 46:51.722
He wore them down, so by the time
they got to me, they were too tired to care.

46:53.641 --> 46:55.672
That is lucky.

46:57.078 --> 47:00.415
- Ignore it.
- Do you have any brothers or sisters?

47:00.515 --> 47:02.951
- I do.
- Good. So they can share the load.

47:03.051 --> 47:06.219
- How many?
- Two.

47:08.756 --> 47:10.536
One.

47:15.580 --> 47:17.904
I have a half-sister.

47:28.576 --> 47:30.587
And I don't...

47:30.929 --> 47:32.846
have a brother.

47:38.620 --> 47:40.787
I... I did...

47:41.723 --> 47:44.824
but I now don't.

47:48.896 --> 47:51.834
Oh, my God! It's worse!

47:51.934 --> 47:55.270
My arms! After all these times,
how can it be worse?

47:55.370 --> 47:58.205
- Sure you want a lesson every day?
- I'm sure.

47:59.473 --> 48:02.728
- Paddling hard, good for you.
- But I'm not getting anywhere.

48:02.828 --> 48:05.447
Well, just for today,

48:05.547 --> 48:09.248
if you can catch me,
I'll give you a ride.

48:36.477 --> 48:40.027
Can I ask you? How?

48:44.652 --> 48:47.822
He was... little.

48:47.922 --> 48:49.589
He...

48:50.557 --> 48:52.314
choked.

48:52.810 --> 48:54.544
Very quickly.

48:55.463 --> 48:58.166
- Your poor parents.
- Yeah.

48:58.266 --> 49:01.168
