01:18:37.577 --> 01:18:39.523
That's a nice one.

01:18:41.314 --> 01:18:43.247
Right?

01:18:51.056 --> 01:18:52.803
- Man, I wish I were you.
- No kidding.

01:18:52.903 --> 01:18:55.762
Everyone will be out of the ocean
a week from now. It'll be all yours.

01:18:55.862 --> 01:18:57.831
Do you wish you were me?

01:18:58.231 --> 01:19:00.058
No, I like it.

01:19:00.158 --> 01:19:03.337
Good teachers, lame teachers,
the boring reading, all of it.

01:19:03.437 --> 01:19:05.341
You'll have fun though.

01:19:05.441 --> 01:19:09.759
You can live like, what's his name,
your surf guy. That can be you.

01:19:10.576 --> 01:19:14.612
- It was a fun summer.
- It really was.

01:19:31.765 --> 01:19:32.896
Thank you.

01:19:51.751 --> 01:19:54.019
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Hello?

01:19:54.119 --> 01:19:57.121
- I'm dialing you.
- I'm dialing you too.

01:20:02.361 --> 01:20:06.130
I would like to see you.
Can I make a time to see you?

01:20:07.966 --> 01:20:11.970
<i>If I told you where to meet me,
would you come here?</i>

01:20:26.486 --> 01:20:29.087
- He's here.
- Gotcha.

01:20:44.837 --> 01:20:49.774
- Hey, I think we met before. Ian.
- Right, hey. How you doing?

01:20:50.676 --> 01:20:54.606
- Is my mom here?
- I think I saw her.

01:20:55.548 --> 01:20:56.939
Is that her?

01:22:08.487 --> 01:22:10.555
What's up?

01:22:15.360 --> 01:22:19.665
The most dangerous part of surfing
is entering and exiting the water.

01:22:19.765 --> 01:22:21.849
Yes, it is.

01:22:22.802 --> 01:22:24.561
It is.

01:22:26.605 --> 01:22:29.740
- Jackie.
- Happy birthday.

01:22:30.342 --> 01:22:34.378
- Don't you have a job?
- I was fired.

01:22:35.013 --> 01:22:38.615
Turns out if you just stop
answering your phone...

01:22:39.552 --> 01:22:41.458
So listen.

01:22:42.254 --> 01:22:44.290
There's no way else to say this.

01:22:45.190 --> 01:22:46.872
There's no way
you're not going to hate it.

01:22:46.972 --> 01:22:50.035
In fact, I don't think there's any way you're
gonna do anything other than scream at me

01:22:50.135 --> 01:22:52.932
and forbid me from doing it,

01:22:53.032 --> 01:22:55.451
but I'm staying.

01:22:55.868 --> 01:22:58.603
- Staying where?
- In Los Angeles.

01:22:59.471 --> 01:23:02.875
There's no point in talking
about collective IQ.

01:23:02.975 --> 01:23:05.111
There's no sport in it.

01:23:05.211 --> 01:23:08.548
By the time you drive to a museum
you've lost the will to look at a painting,

01:23:08.648 --> 01:23:10.999
so it's hardly a decision
based on culture,

01:23:12.084 --> 01:23:14.485
but I'm staying.

01:23:14.787 --> 01:23:16.021
Here.

01:23:18.757 --> 01:23:20.389
I'm going to say something.

01:23:21.593 --> 01:23:26.689
And I don't care if you believe me,
because I'll prove it to be true.

01:23:28.467 --> 01:23:30.907
You don't have to see me.

01:23:31.303 --> 01:23:34.607
I'll be here. If I see you somewhere,
if I run into you,

01:23:34.707 --> 01:23:38.344
I'll say hello and let you go
on your way.

01:23:39.144 --> 01:23:42.382
You know I'd give everything I might ever
hope to have to spend time with you,

01:23:42.482 --> 01:23:44.949
but if you don't want that...

01:23:46.785 --> 01:23:48.853
it's okay.

01:23:52.908 --> 01:23:54.980
I just need nothing.

01:23:55.928 --> 01:23:59.999
Do you mean you need something,
or that you don't need anything?

01:24:00.099 --> 01:24:03.067
Being here is corrupting
your English, Jackie.

01:24:04.136 --> 01:24:06.563
I need nothing.

01:24:07.039 --> 01:24:09.640
The nothing that is here.

01:24:11.210 --> 01:24:13.777
- So...
- I'm going back.

01:24:14.046 --> 01:24:16.382
I begged the school.

01:24:16.882 --> 01:24:19.985
Blamed it on you, which seemed to work.

01:24:20.085 --> 01:24:22.553
They're taking me back.

01:24:23.555 --> 01:24:25.923
I'm leaving tomorrow.

01:24:27.493 --> 01:24:29.170
Good luck.

01:24:31.029 --> 01:24:35.132
- It's okay, you can say you'll miss me.
- I'll miss you so much.

01:24:38.569 --> 01:24:41.673
You know, I've pissed away
a good amount of our money here.

01:24:41.773 --> 01:24:46.777
Was your father on board with this
crazy school thing you're wanting to do?

01:24:47.746 --> 01:24:51.415
- He is.
- What did he say?

01:24:51.951 --> 01:24:54.401
Whatever makes me happy.

01:24:55.387 --> 01:24:57.754
How does he do that?

01:25:00.092 --> 01:25:02.526
I don't want to live to work.

01:25:06.665 --> 01:25:10.703
- Okay.
- I will see you. I'll be around.

01:25:10.803 --> 01:25:13.137
You'll go there.

01:25:14.373 --> 01:25:16.403
Life is long.

01:25:18.110 --> 01:25:19.550
It is.

01:25:21.646 --> 01:25:23.866
What was the idea...

01:25:23.966 --> 01:25:26.318
for the end of the story?

01:25:26.418 --> 01:25:28.688
That she jumps.

01:25:28.788 --> 01:25:31.092
And she falls.

01:25:32.391 --> 01:25:34.862
And nothing catches her.

01:25:34.962 --> 01:25:37.973
And she cracks her head open and dies.

01:25:40.104 --> 01:25:42.694
It might need a little work.

01:25:44.970 --> 01:25:47.907
- Carry your board?
- Thank you, Angelo.

01:25:48.007 --> 01:25:50.229
You got it, kidget.

01:25:51.610 --> 01:25:53.692
Did you bring your board?

